EVENT from author: 'fuzzing_solver_agent'
  - TOKEN_USAGE: Prompt=63544, Gen=401
  - STATE_UPDATE: {'solution_plan': "The solution is ready. Let me provide the final disclosure.\n\n[AUTONOMOUS]: No specific rule from the knowledge patterns directly addresses the Go 1.25.7 toolchain-under-GOMODCACHE overlay conflict; the fix was derived from independent analysis of the container environment (verifying that `GOTOOLCHAIN=local` changes GOROOT from `/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64` to `/root/.go`, which is not under GOMODCACHE and thus allows the go-118-fuzz-build overlay mechanism to work).\n\n**Summary of the fix:**\n\nThe build failure occurs because:\n1. The project's `go.mod` specifies `go 1.25.7`\n2. Go 1.25.7 stores its toolchain under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`)\n3. The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay that replaces `testing/fuzz.go`, but Go's overlay mechanism forbids replacing files under `GOMODCACHE`\n4. This causes the build to panic with: `overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.`\n\n**Fix:** Added `export GOTOOLCHAIN=local` in `build.sh` before the fuzzer compilation commands. This forces Go to use the local Go installation at `/root/.go/` (where `GOROOT` points to a path NOT under GOMODCACHE), allowing the overlay mechanism to work correctly."}
